<subSubSection lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="492" pageId="0" pageNumber="491" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1760,2026]" pageId="0" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,1760,1783]" pageId="0" pageNumber="491">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The genus includes only three species, two of those, 
<taxonomicName box="[833,948,1760,1783]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypobarathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="repetita">
<emphasis box="[833,948,1760,1783]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="491">H. repetita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[999,1068,1760,1783]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypobarathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rau" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[999,1068,1760,1783]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="491">H. rau</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1075,1134,1760,1783]" pageId="0" pageNumber="491">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1075,1134,1760,1783]" pageId="0" pageNumber="491" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, are similar in size, reddishbrown colouration of the thorax and forewings, while the third species, 
<taxonomicName box="[950,1066,1795,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="icterias">
<emphasis box="[950,1066,1795,1818]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="491">H. icterias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is remarkably smaller and has a yellowish-orange coloured forewings mixed with brownish scales. Antennae of both sexes filiform, forewings elongated triangular in shape with apex moderately acute, in 
<taxonomicName box="[719,838,1864,1887]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypobarathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="repetita">
<emphasis box="[719,838,1864,1887]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="491">H. repetita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[897,970,1864,1887]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypobarathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rau">
<emphasis box="[897,970,1864,1887]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="491">H. rau</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, more rounded on females of 
<taxonomicName box="[1313,1429,1864,1887]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="icterias">
<emphasis box="[1313,1429,1864,1887]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="491">H. icterias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Reniform stigma large, remarkable, orbicular and claviform stigmata, antemedian and postmedian fasciae indistinct, subterminal fascia remarkable and strongly waved on 
<taxonomicName box="[732,845,1933,1956]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="icterias">
<emphasis box="[732,845,1933,1956]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="491">H. icterias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[898,968,1933,1956]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypobarathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rau">
<emphasis box="[898,968,1933,1956]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="491">H. rau</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but less distinct on 
<taxonomicName box="[1190,1305,1933,1956]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypobarathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="repetita">
<emphasis box="[1190,1305,1933,1956]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="491">H. repetita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Hindwings rather dark-greyish on 
<taxonomicName box="[394,509,1968,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypobarathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="repetita">
<emphasis box="[394,509,1968,1991]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="491">H. repetita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[560,629,1968,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypobarathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rau">
<emphasis box="[560,629,1968,1991]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="491">H. rau</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, lighter yellowish-white on 
<taxonomicName box="[931,1043,1968,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="icterias">
<emphasis box="[931,1043,1968,1991]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="491">H. icterias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, discal spot well expressed, terminal shade broad and pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,152,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="492">
The male genitalia show the typical characters of most Hadeninae-genera in their ground plan, maybe only the subapically less strongly angled and narrower valva can be mentioned as unique feature of 
<emphasis box="[1132,1291,185,210]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="492">
<taxonomicName box="[1132,1285,185,209]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypobarathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hypobarathra</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The cucullus is completely differently shaped on all three species: rather broad, spatulate on 
<taxonomicName box="[1007,1120,221,244]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="icterias">
<emphasis box="[1007,1120,221,244]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="492">H. icterias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, falcate, apically acute on 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypobarathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="repetita">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="492">H. repetita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with an additional small, acute apical process and narrow, rounded, finger-shaped on 
<taxonomicName box="[1150,1212,256,279]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypobarathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rau">
<emphasis box="[1150,1212,256,279]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="492">H.rau</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The short but broad aedeagus and vesica are very similar to those of 
<taxonomicName box="[667,784,289,313]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Melanchra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[667,784,289,313]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="492">Melanchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, just as the main characters of the female genitalia.
</paragraph>
